(sv)

En slags klipp-och-klistra-variant p&aring; en "best of"-skiva.
En melodi h&auml;rifr&aring;n, en text j&auml;rifr&aring;n, en refr&auml;ng h&auml;rifr&aring;n,
en keyboard fr&aring;n gud-vet-vart och vips s&aring; har man en ny fr&auml;sch l&aring;t.

F&ouml;rsta sp&aring;ret b&ouml;rjar med en virvel som tydligen &auml;r en v&auml;ldigt
f&ouml;rvr&auml;ngd variant p&aring; virveln fr&aring;n ledmotivet till Freakshow.
Sen h&ouml;rs en kuslig orgel som visar sig spela melodin fr&aring;n
"the Walrus Hunt". N&auml;r trummorna sedan kommer in s&aring; visar det sig
att de har med basg&aring;ngen fr&aring;n Diskomo-versionen av samma l&aring;t.
Till sist b&ouml;rjar s&aring;ngaren sjunga texten fr&aring;n "Loss Of Innocense".

&Auml;ven om man h&ouml;rt alla l&aring;tarna f&ouml;rut
s&aring; liknar det inte n&aring;gon av dem.

P&aring; andra l&aring;tar har de &auml;ven l&aring;nat fr&aring;n l&aring;tar av/med Snakefinger och Renaldo & the Loaf.


(eng)

Sort of a cut-and-paste-styled "best of" album.
A melodi from here, lyrics from here, a chorus from here,
a keyboard from god-knows-where and there you have it,
a fresh new song.

The first track starts with a drum drill that is a very
warped version of the one from the Freakshow theme.
Then we hear an eerie organ which apparently is playing
the melodi from "the Walrus Hunt". When the drums join in,
it turns out they've used the bassline from the Diskmo version
of the same song. Finally, the singer starts singing the lyrics
from "Loss Of Innocense".

Even if you've heard all of the songs before,
this doesn't sound like any of them.

On other songs, they have also borrowed from songs
by/with Snakefinger, as well as Renaldo & the Loaf.
